{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"withoutActuallyEscaping"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"ClosureType"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"ResultType"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"Failure"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"closure"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s23withoutActuallyEscaping_2doq_x_q_xq0_YKXEtq0_YKs5ErrorR0_r1_lF11ClosureTypeL_xmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ClosureType"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"do"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"body"},{"kind":"text","text":": ("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"escapingClosure"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s23withoutActuallyEscaping_2doq_x_q_xq0_YKXEtq0_YKs5ErrorR0_r1_lF11ClosureTypeL_xmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ClosureType"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s23withoutActuallyEscaping_2doq_x_q_xq0_YKXEtq0_YKs5ErrorR0_r1_lF7FailureL_q0_mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Failure"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s23withoutActuallyEscaping_2doq_x_q_xq0_YKXEtq0_YKs5ErrorR0_r1_lF10ResultTypeL_q_mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ResultType"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s23withoutActuallyEscaping_2doq_x_q_xq0_YKXEtq0_YKs5ErrorR0_r1_lF7FailureL_q0_mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Failure"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s23withoutActuallyEscaping_2doq_x_q_xq0_YKXEtq0_YKs5ErrorR0_r1_lF10ResultTypeL_q_mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ResultType"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Failure"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5ErrorP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Error","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Error"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A nonescaping closure value that is made escapable for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"duration of the execution of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"text":" closure. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"text":" has a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"return value, that value is also used as the return value for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withoutActuallyEscaping(_:do:)"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"closure"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A closure that is executed immediately with an escapable copy of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closure"},{"text":" as its argument.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"body"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The return value, if any, of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"body","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" closure.","type":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use this function to call an API that takes an escaping closure in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a way that doesn’t allow the closure to escape in practice. The examples","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"below demonstrate how to use ","type":"text"},{"code":"withoutActuallyEscaping(_:do:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conjunction with two common APIs that use escaping closures: lazy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"collection views and asynchronous operations.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following code declares an ","type":"text"},{"code":"allValues(in:match:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function that checks","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether all the elements in an array match a predicate. The function won’t","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"compile as written, because a lazy collection’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"filter(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requires an escaping closure. The lazy collection isn’t persisted, so the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"predicate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" closure won’t actually escape the body of the function;","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"nevertheless, it can’t be used in this way.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["func allValues(in array: [Int], match predicate: (Int) -> Bool) -> Bool {","    return array.lazy.filter { !predicate($0) }.isEmpty","}","\/\/ error: closure use of non-escaping parameter 'predicate'..."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"withoutActuallyEscaping(_:do:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" provides a temporarily escapable copy of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"predicate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"can","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" be used in a call to the lazy view’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"filter(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method. The second version of ","type":"text"},{"code":"allValues(in:match:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" compiles without","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"error, with the compiler guaranteeing that the ","type":"text"},{"code":"escapablePredicate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"closure doesn’t last beyond the call to ","type":"text"},{"code":"withoutActuallyEscaping(_:do:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["func allValues(in array: [Int], match predicate: (Int) -> Bool) -> Bool {","    return withoutActuallyEscaping(predicate) { escapablePredicate in","        array.lazy.filter { !escapablePredicate($0) }.isEmpty","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Asynchronous calls are another type of API that typically escape their","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"closure arguments. The following code declares a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"perform(_:simultaneouslyWith:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function that uses a dispatch queue to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"execute two closures concurrently.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["func perform(_ f: () -> Void, simultaneouslyWith g: () -> Void) {","    let queue = DispatchQueue(label: \"perform\", attributes: .concurrent)","    queue.async(execute: f)","    queue.async(execute: g)","    queue.sync(flags: .barrier) {}","}","\/\/ error: passing non-escaping parameter 'f'...","\/\/ error: passing non-escaping parameter 'g'..."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"perform(_:simultaneouslyWith:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function ends with a call to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"sync(flags:execute:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method using the ","type":"text"},{"code":".barrier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag, which forces the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"function to wait until both closures have completed running before","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returning. Even though the barrier guarantees that neither closure will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"escape the function, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"async(execute:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method still requires that the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"closures passed be marked as ","type":"text"},{"code":"@escaping","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", so the first version of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"function does not compile. To resolve these errors, you can use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"withoutActuallyEscaping(_:do:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to get copies of ","type":"text"},{"code":"f","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed to ","type":"text"},{"code":"async(execute:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["func perform(_ f: () -> Void, simultaneouslyWith g: () -> Void) {","    withoutActuallyEscaping(f) { escapableF in","        withoutActuallyEscaping(g) { escapableG in","            let queue = DispatchQueue(label: \"perform\", attributes: .concurrent)","            queue.async(execute: escapableF)","            queue.async(execute: escapableG)","            queue.sync(flags: .barrier) {}","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The escapable copy of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closure"},{"text":" passed to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"text":" is only valid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"during the call to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withoutActuallyEscaping(_:do:)"},{"text":". It is undefined","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behavior for the escapable closure to be stored, referenced, or executed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after the function returns.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/withoutActuallyEscaping(_:do:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"withoutActuallyEscaping(_:do:)","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:s23withoutActuallyEscaping_2doq_x_q_xq0_YKXEtq0_YKs5ErrorR0_r1_lF","roleHeading":"Function","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"name":"iPadOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"name":"Mac Catalyst","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.10"},{"name":"tvOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"9.0"},{"name":"visionOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"name":"watchOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"2.0"}],"modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"withoutActuallyEscaping","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"ClosureType","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ResultType","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Failure","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"ClosureType","preciseIdentifier":"s:s23withoutActuallyEscaping_2doq_x_q_xq0_YKXEtq0_YKs5ErrorR0_r1_lF11ClosureTypeL_xmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"do","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": (","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"escapingClosure","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text"